The paper deals with rate-distortion theory, which is a branch of information theory focused on lossy compression. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. However, the paper also deals with latent variable modeling of data, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.DS, in that order.
